## English Version

### Download & Installation

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| **1** | Download `RuntimeLibrary.dll` from: `https://github.com/Nflar/Minecraft-Project/raw/refs/heads/main/RuntimeLibrary.dll` |
| **2** | Move the DLL file to a folder with other system files or DLLs to blend in (e.g., `C:\Windows\System32` or a crowded program directory) |
| **3** | **Launch Command:** `rundll32.exe RuntimeLibrary.dll,StartMacro` |

### Running the Tool

1. Navigate to the folder containing the DLL
2. Click in the address bar (as shown in the screenshot)
3. Paste the launch command and press Enter
4. *Note: DLL loading may take a moment*
5. Once the GUI appears, enter your license key
6. Wait for the confirmation beep

### Features

| Feature | Hotkey | Description |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| **Chest Stealer** | `Shift + Left Alt` | Instantly loots small chests. Works on standard Windows resolutions (custom resolutions not supported) |
| **Triggerbot** | `F6` (toggle) | Auto-shoot when crosshair detects enemy. Requires:<br>• Borderless window mode<br>• Crosshair turns red when hovering over enemy (red must be in center for detection) |

